longInfo:
Passport required.
- Nationals of Austria are allowed to enter with an expired
  passport. The passport is accepted when expired for a
  maximum of 1 year. 
- Nationals of Austria traveling without a passport must have
  a document accepted for entry, valid on arrival.
  
Passport Exemptions:
- Holders of a National ID Card issued to nationals of
  Austria. 

VISA NOT REQUIRED.

Minors:
- WARNING! In accordance with European Union (EU) Legislation,
  all minors who are nationals of Austria will be expected to
  hold their own passport or National ID Card (where
  applicable) when departing from Bulgaria, Croatia, Cyprus,
  Romania or a Schengen Member State . 
- All minors who are nationals of Austria are expected to hold
  their own travel document.
Additional Information:
- A valid residence permit in an expired or invalidated travel
  document is accepted provided holding a valid travel
  document
